		<section>
			<p><img src="C:\Users\ma852\Desktop\bus.jpg" alt="bus" class="mainimg"/>
			Steptoe Butte is a quartzite island jutting out of the silty loess of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palouse">Paluse</a>hills in whiteman County, Washington. The rock that forms the butte is over 400 million years old, in contrast with the 16-7 million year old<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Columbia_River">Columbia River</a>basalts that underlie the rest of the Palouse (such islands of ancient rock have come to be called buttes, a butte being defined as a small hill with a flat top, whose width at top does not exceed its height)</p>
			<p>A hotel built by Cashup Davis stood atop Steptoe Butte from Virgil McCroskey donated 120 acres of land to form arecs. Steptoe Btte os currently recognized as a National Natural Landmark because of its unique geological value.It is named in honor of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colonel_Edward_Steptoe">Colonel Edward Steptoe</a>.</p>
		</section>
		
